    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That sounds like a pretty clear way of putting it, but isn't there an argument that social spending actually helps the economy in the long run? Like, if people are healthier and have more support, they're more productive, which grows the economy and helps the debt naturally. Doesn't focusing too hard on debt reduction actually risk hurting the very growth you're talking about?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
