      "content": "i get that, but it feels like you're basically saying debt reduction is the prerequisite for everything else. if we're talking about \"fiscal discipline,\" isn't that just a polite way of saying we should prioritize balanced budgets over the actual needs of the people right now? it feels like your advice is leaning heavily towards a specific conservative way of looking at things rather than looking at the human cost of cutting spending.",
